==English==
=== Etymology ===
From {{Sp.}} ''[[latinoamericano]]'', Latin American &gt; {{Sp.}} ''[[latino#Spanish|latino]]'' (''adj''), Latin [http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/latino] &gt; {{L.}} ''[[latinus]]''

===Proper noun===
'''Latino'''
# A person of Spanish (or Portuguese) descent.
#:''There are many famous Latinos in the music world.''
# A person from Latin America, (or sometimes even Spain).
# A person residing in the United States, who is of Spanish or Latin American descent.
#:''Latinos are quickly becoming the largest minority in the United States.''

===Adjective=== 
# of Latin American or Spanish descent 

